'''Otto Fl<U+00FC>gel''' (1842, L<U+00FC>tzen - 1914, D<U+00F6>lau, [[Halle (Saale)|Halle]]) was a [[Germany|German]] [[philosopher]] and [[theologian]].

==Biography==
He studied at [[Schulpforta]] and [[University of Halle|Halle]], and took up pastoral work. He was made editor of the ''Zeitschrift f<U+00FC>r exacte Philosophie im Sinne des Neueren Philosophischen Realismus'' (<U+201C>Journal for exact philosophy in the sense of the newer [[philosophical realism]]<U+201D>), and in 1894 was one of the founders of ''Zeitschrift f<U+00FC>r Philosophie und P<U+00E4>dagogik''. He was a supporter of [[Herbartian]] realism, as opposed to New-[[Kantian]] speculations, yet he believed in the necessity of a revelation.

==Works==
Among his works may be mentioned:
* ''Die Spekulative Theologie der Gegenwart'' (<U+201C>Speculative theology of the present<U+201D>)
* ''Das Ich und die sittliche Idee im Leben der V<U+00F6>lker'' (<U+201C>The ego and the moral idea in the life of peoples,<U+201D> 1892)
* ''<U+00DC>ber die pers<U+00F6>nliche Unsterblichkeit'' (<U+201C>On personal immortality,<U+201D> 1902)
* ''Monismus und Theologie'' (<U+201C>[[Monism]] and theology,<U+201D> 1908)

